foods.name: Chicken Biryani
foods.description: Fragrant basmati rice with spiced chicken and aromatic herbs.
foods.more_info: A classic Indian rice dish, layered with marinated chicken, fragrant basmati, and spices like saffron, cardamom, and cloves. Traditionally cooked in a sealed pot to enhance flavor.

foods.name: Butter Chicken
foods.description: Creamy tomato curry with tender chicken and warm spices.
foods.more_info: Tender chicken simmered in a rich tomato and butter-based curry sauce with mild spices, making it creamy and comforting. Often served with naan or rice.

foods.name: Masala Dosa
foods.description: Crispy rice-lentil crepe filled with spiced potato masala.
foods.more_info: A popular South Indian breakfast item, this thin, crispy crepe made from fermented rice and lentils is filled with a savory potato and spice mix, usually served with coconut chutney and sambar.

foods.name: Samosa
foods.description: Golden fried pastry with a savory spiced filling.
foods.more_info: A triangular, deep-fried pastry stuffed with spiced potatoes, peas, or meat. A popular Indian snack and street food.

foods.name: Palak Paneer
foods.description: Creamy spinach curry with soft paneer cheese cubes.
foods.more_info: Palak Paneer is a creamy curry made with spinach and soft cubes of paneer cheese. It's often served with naan or rice.

foods.name: Jollof Rice
foods.description: Tomato-pepper rice with deep, smoky flavor and gentle heat.
foods.more_info: A West African classic, Jollof rice is cooked with tomatoes, peppers, onions, and often seasoned with thyme and bay leaves. Can include meat or seafood.

foods.name: Suya
foods.description: Char-grilled skewers with a bold peanut-spice seasoning.
foods.more_info: A popular Nigerian street food of skewered beef, chicken, or goat, coated with a spicy peanut seasoning and grilled over open flames.

foods.name: Egusi Soup
foods.description: Hearty melon-seed stew with rich flavor and comforting heat.
foods.more_info: A Nigerian stew made with ground melon seeds, leafy vegetables, and meat or fish. Thick, nutty, and rich in flavor, usually eaten with fufu or rice.

foods.name: Puff Puff
foods.description: Soft, sweet fried dough bites — perfect for sharing.
foods.more_info: A West African sweet snack made from deep-fried dough, light and fluffy inside, golden brown outside, often dusted with sugar.

foods.name: Pizza Margherita
foods.description: Classic tomato, mozzarella, and basil on a crisp crust.
foods.more_info: Traditional Italian pizza featuring a thin, crisp crust topped with tomato sauce, fresh mozzarella, and basil leaves. Iconic for its simplicity and balanced flavors.

foods.name: Spaghetti Carbonara
foods.description: Silky egg-and-cheese sauce with pepper and crisp pancetta.
foods.more_info: Classic Roman pasta dish with a creamy egg, parmesan, and pecorino cheese sauce, tossed with crispy pancetta and black pepper.

foods.name: Lasagna
foods.description: Layered pasta baked with rich sauce and melted cheese.
foods.more_info: Baked Italian pasta dish with alternating layers of pasta sheets, meat or vegetables, tomato sauce, and cheese, creating a hearty and comforting meal.

foods.name: Tiramisu
foods.description: Coffee-soaked layers with mascarpone cream and cocoa.
foods.more_info: Famous Italian dessert of coffee-soaked ladyfingers layered with mascarpone cream and dusted with cocoa powder for a light yet decadent treat.

foods.name: Mushroom Risotto
foods.description: Creamy arborio rice with wild mushrooms and parmesan.
foods.more_info: Italian risotto made from slow-cooked arborio rice in stock, finished with butter, parmesan, and earthy mushrooms for a rich, creamy texture.

foods.name: Sushi Platter
foods.description: A variety of nigiri and rolls with wasabi and soy sauce.
foods.more_info: Japanese dish of bite-sized rice and seafood combinations, including raw fish (sashimi) and rolls, served with soy sauce, pickled ginger, and wasabi.

foods.name: Miso Ramen
foods.description: Warm miso broth with noodles and savory toppings.
foods.more_info: Japanese noodle soup with miso-flavored broth, topped with vegetables, meat, and sometimes egg. Savory, umami-rich, and comforting.

foods.name: Chicken Teriyaki Bowl
foods.description: Sweet-savory glazed chicken served over steamed rice.
foods.more_info: Japanese rice bowl topped with tender chicken glazed in sweet-savory teriyaki sauce, often garnished with sesame seeds and green onions.

foods.name: Tempura
foods.description: Light and crispy battered seafood and vegetables.
foods.more_info: Japanese dish of seafood or vegetables lightly battered and deep-fried to a delicate crisp, served with dipping sauce.

foods.name: Pad Thai
foods.description: Stir-fried rice noodles with tangy tamarind and crushed peanuts.
foods.more_info: Pad Thai is a popular Thai dish made with stir-fried rice noodles, tangy tamarind sauce, and crushed peanuts. It's often served with lime wedges and bean sprouts.

foods.name: Thai Green Curry
foods.description: Coconut green curry with herbs and a fragrant kick.
foods.more_info: Thai Green Curry is a flavorful curry made with coconut milk, green curry paste, and a variety of herbs and vegetables. It has a fragrant kick and is often served with rice.

foods.name: Tom Yum Soup
foods.description: Hot and sour soup with lemongrass, shrimp, and chili.
foods.more_info: Tom Yum Soup is a flavorful Thai soup made with lemongrass, shrimp, and chili. It has a fragrant kick and is often served with rice.

foods.name: Falafel
foods.description: Crispy chickpea fritters with herbs and warm spices.
foods.more_info: Falafel is a popular Middle Eastern dish made with crispy chickpea fritters seasoned with herbs and warm spices. It's often served in pita bread with tahini sauce.

foods.name: Chicken Shawarma Wrap
foods.description: Juicy chicken, pickles, and garlic sauce in warm flatbread.
foods.more_info: Marinated chicken cooked on a vertical spit, sliced, and wrapped in flatbread with garlic sauce, pickles, and vegetables. A popular Middle Eastern street food.

foods.name: Hummus Plate
foods.description: Smooth chickpea dip with tahini, lemon, and olive oil.
foods.more_info: Classic Middle Eastern dip made from blended chickpeas, tahini, olive oil, lemon juice, and garlic. Often served with pita bread or vegetables.

foods.name: Cheeseburger
foods.description: Grilled beef patty with cheese, pickles, and house sauce.
foods.more_info: A Cheeseburger is a classic American dish made with a grilled beef patty, cheese, pickles, and house sauce on a bun. It's often served with fries or a side salad.

foods.name: Classic Hot Dog
foods.description: Grilled frankfurter in a soft bun with classic toppings.
foods.more_info: A Classic Hot Dog is a popular American fast food made with a grilled frankfurter in a soft bun, topped with classic condiments like mustard, ketchup, and relish.

foods.name: Tacos al Pastor
foods.description: Marinated pork shaved from the spit with bright toppings.
foods.more_info: Tacos al Pastor is a popular Mexican dish made with marinated pork shaved from a spit, served with bright toppings like pineapple, onions, and cilantro.

foods.name: Guacamole & Chips
foods.description: Fresh avocado dip with lime, cilantro, and tortilla chips.
foods.more_info: Guacamole & Chips is a popular Mexican snack made with fresh avocado dip seasoned with lime, cilantro, and served with tortilla chips.

foods.name: Seafood Paella
foods.description: Saffron rice with seafood and Mediterranean flavor.
foods.more_info: Seafood Paella is a classic Spanish dish made with saffron rice, a variety of seafood, and Mediterranean flavors. It's often served with lemon wedges.

foods.name: Tapas Platter
foods.description: Assorted Spanish small plates with olives, cheese, and meats.
foods.more_info: A Tapas Platter is a selection of assorted Spanish small plates featuring olives, cheese, and meats. It's perfect for sharing and exploring different flavors.

foods.name: Kung Pao Chicken
foods.description: Stir-fried chicken with peanuts, chili, and a savory glaze.
foods.more_info: Kung Pao Chicken is a popular Chinese dish made with stir-fried chicken, peanuts, chili, and a savory glaze. It's often served with rice.

foods.name: Dim Sum Basket
foods.description: Steamed dumplings filled with pork and shrimp.
foods.more_info: A Dim Sum Basket is a selection of steamed dumplings filled with pork and shrimp. It's a popular choice for dim sum brunch.

foods.name: Bibimbap
foods.description: Warm rice bowl with vegetables, egg, and gochujang.
foods.more_info: Bibimbap is a Korean dish made with a warm rice bowl topped with vegetables, egg, and gochujang (a spicy red pepper paste). It's often mixed together before eating.

foods.name: Kimchi
foods.description: Fermented spicy cabbage with bold, tangy flavor.
foods.more_info: Kimchi is a traditional Korean side dish made with fermented spicy cabbage. It has a bold, tangy flavor and is often served with rice and other dishes.

foods.name: Croissant
foods.description: Buttery, flaky pastry fresh from the oven.
foods.more_info: A Croissant is a buttery, flaky pastry that is fresh from the oven. It's a popular breakfast item and is often served with coffee or tea.

foods.name: Ratatouille
foods.description: Provençal stewed vegetables in rich tomato sauce.
foods.more_info: Ratatouille is a classic French dish made with Provençal stewed vegetables in a rich tomato sauce. It's often served as a side dish or main course.

foods.name: Crème Brûlée
foods.description: Vanilla custard with caramelized sugar crust.
foods.more_info: Crème Brûlée is a classic French dessert made with vanilla custard topped with a caramelized sugar crust. It's a rich and indulgent treat.

foods.name: Coq au Vin
foods.description: Chicken braised in red wine with mushrooms and onions.
foods.more_info: Coq au Vin is a classic French dish made with chicken braised in red wine with mushrooms and onions. It's a rich and flavorful stew.

foods.name: Pho
foods.description: Aromatic beef noodle soup with fresh herbs.
foods.more_info: Pho is a classic Vietnamese dish made with aromatic beef noodle soup and fresh herbs. It's often served with lime wedges and bean sprouts.

foods.name: Banh Mi
foods.description: Crispy baguette with savory pork, pickles, and cilantro.
foods.more_info: Banh Mi is a popular Vietnamese sandwich made with a crispy baguette filled with savory pork, pickles, and cilantro. It's often served with a side of spicy mayo.

foods.name: Fresh Spring Rolls
foods.description: Rice paper rolls filled with herbs, shrimp, and vermicelli.
foods.more_info: Fresh Spring Rolls are a popular Vietnamese dish made with rice paper rolls filled with herbs, shrimp, and vermicelli. They're often served with a peanut dipping sauce.

foods.name: Moussaka
foods.description: Layered eggplant and meat with creamy béchamel topping.
foods.more_info: Moussaka is a classic Greek dish made with layered eggplant and meat, topped with a creamy béchamel sauce. It's often served with a side salad.

foods.name: Chicken Souvlaki
foods.description: Grilled chicken skewers with tzatziki and pita bread.
foods.more_info: Chicken Souvlaki is a popular Greek dish made with grilled chicken skewers served with tzatziki and pita bread. It's often served with a side of fries or salad.

foods.name: Greek Salad
foods.description: Fresh tomatoes, cucumber, olives, and feta cheese.
foods.more_info: Greek Salad is a classic Greek dish made with fresh tomatoes, cucumber, olives, and feta cheese. It's often served with a side of pita bread.

foods.name: Baklava
foods.description: Sweet phyllo pastry with honey and chopped nuts.
foods.more_info: Baklava is a classic Greek dessert made with sweet phyllo pastry layered with honey and chopped nuts. It's a rich and indulgent treat.

foods.name: Feijoada
foods.description: Hearty black bean stew with pork and beef.
foods.more_info: Feijoada is a classic Brazilian dish made with hearty black bean stew with pork and beef. It's often served with rice and collard greens.

foods.name: Picanha Steak
foods.description: Grilled top sirloin cap with coarse salt.
foods.more_info: Picanha Steak is a classic Brazilian dish made with grilled top sirloin cap seasoned with coarse salt. It's often served with a side of rice and beans.

foods.name: Pão de Queijo
foods.description: Cheesy Brazilian bread rolls, crispy outside and soft inside.
foods.more_info: Pão de Queijo is a popular Brazilian snack made with cheesy bread rolls that are crispy on the outside and soft on the inside. They're often served with coffee or tea.

foods.name: Injera with Doro Wat
foods.description: Spongy flatbread with spicy chicken stew.
foods.more_info: Injera with Doro Wat is a classic Ethiopian dish made with spongy flatbread served with spicy chicken stew. It's often served with a side of vegetables.

foods.name: Kitfo
foods.description: Seasoned raw minced beef with spiced butter.
foods.more_info: Kitfo is a traditional Ethiopian dish made with seasoned raw minced beef mixed with spiced butter. It's often served with injera bread.

foods.name: Tibs
foods.description: Sautéed meat with vegetables and aromatic spices.
foods.more_info: Tibs is a popular Ethiopian dish made with sautéed meat, vegetables, and aromatic spices. It's often served with injera bread.

foods.name: Turkish Kebab
foods.description: Grilled seasoned meat on skewers with vegetables.
foods.more_info: Turkish Kebab is a popular dish made with grilled seasoned meat on skewers served with vegetables. It's often served with rice or flatbread.

foods.name: Lahmacun
foods.description: Thin flatbread topped with spiced minced meat.
foods.more_info: Lahmacun is a popular Turkish dish made with thin flatbread topped with spiced minced meat. It's often served with a side of salad or yogurt.

foods.name: Jerk Chicken
foods.description: Spicy grilled chicken with allspice and Scotch bonnet peppers.
foods.more_info: Jerk Chicken is a popular Caribbean dish made with spicy grilled chicken seasoned with allspice and Scotch bonnet peppers. It's often served with rice and peas.

foods.name: Fried Plantains
foods.description: Sweet caramelized plantains, crispy and golden.
foods.more_info: Fried Plantains are a popular Caribbean side dish made with sweet caramelized plantains that are crispy and golden. They're often served with rice and beans.

foods.name: Moroccan Tagine
foods.description: Slow-cooked stew with lamb, vegetables, and warm spices.
foods.more_info: Moroccan Tagine is a classic dish made with slow-cooked stew featuring lamb, vegetables, and warm spices. It's often served with couscous or bread.

foods.name: Couscous
foods.description: Fluffy semolina with vegetables and aromatic broth.
foods.more_info: Couscous is a Moroccan dish made with fluffy semolina with vegetables and aromatic broth.

foods.name: Wiener Schnitzel
foods.description: Breaded and fried veal cutlet with lemon.
foods.more_info: Wiener Schnitzel is a classic German dish made with breaded and fried veal cutlet with lemon. It's often served with a side of potatoes or salad.

foods.name: Bratwurst
foods.description: Grilled German sausage with mustard and bread.
foods.more_info: Bratwurst is a popular German dish made with grilled German sausage with mustard and bread. It's often served with potato salad.

foods.name: Soft Pretzel
foods.description: Warm salted pretzel with a golden brown crust.
foods.more_info: Soft Pretzel is a popular German dish made with a warm salted pretzel with a golden brown crust. It's often served with a side of mustard or ketchup.

foods.name: Nasi Goreng
foods.description: Indonesian fried rice with sweet soy sauce and egg.
foods.more_info: Nasi Goreng is a popular Indonesian dish made with fried rice cooked with sweet soy sauce and topped with an egg. It's often served with a side of cucumber.

foods.name: Chicken Satay
foods.description: Grilled chicken skewers with peanut sauce.
foods.more_info: Chicken Satay is a popular Indonesian dish made with grilled chicken skewers served with peanut sauce. It's often served with a side of rice or cucumber salad.

foods.name: Beef Rendang
foods.description: Rich and tender coconut beef curry.
foods.more_info: Beef Rendang is a popular Indonesian dish made with rich and tender coconut beef curry. It's often served with a side of rice.
